00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:13,759
KONG: No, or actually...

454
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,177
- KONG: Not really drunk.
- NAMNUNG: Not drunk but...

455
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:15,719
KONG: Not really drunk, but...

456
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:16,261
NAMNUNG: Just an excuse, huh?

457
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,138
KONG: An excuse to be with them.

458
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:19,890
KONG: And maybe send this message saying...

459
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:21,475
KONG: Hey, tonight...

460
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:22,726
KONG: I'm really drunk.

461
00:18:23,268 --> 00:18:24,353
KONG: My friends got me wasted.

462
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:26,480
KONG: Can I crash at your place?

463
00:18:27,356 --> 00:18:28,440
KONG: Oh, that works.

464
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:30,317
KONG: Yeah, this totally works.

465
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:31,902
NAMNUNG: It works. It really works.

466
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,572
NAMNUNG: I'm not thinking about the person
I'm talking to or my partner at all.

467
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:36,448
NAMNUNG: I'm thinking about my friends.

468
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:38,909
NAMNUNG: My friends have to help me out, you know?

469
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:39,952
NAMNUNG: I won't let them see.

470
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:43,622
NAMNUNG: I'll never let the person I'm talking to
or my partner see me when I'm drunk.

471
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:44,873
NAMNUNG: Otherwise, they'll be like, "Oh, wow."

472
00:18:45,082 --> 00:18:47,042
NAMNUNG: "Totally wasted,
not taking care of yourself at all."

473
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,128
NAMNUNG: I feel like it's better to send it
to my friends instead.

474
00:18:49,336 --> 00:18:51,255
NAMNUNG: I don't want to send it to the person
I'm talking to or my partner.

475
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:53,465
NAMNUNG: Otherwise, if I end up doing
or saying something,

476
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:55,884
NAMNUNG: the whole relationship could fall apart.

477
00:18:56,426 --> 00:18:56,844
KONG: That's true.

478
00:18:57,344 --> 00:18:59,346
KONG: But if you look at it another way,

479
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:01,014
KONG: what if we just want
to act cute with our partner?

480
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,141
NAMNUNG: We just want to act cute with our partner?

481
00:19:02,307 --> 00:19:03,892
NAMNUNG: Then it could change into more like,

482
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:06,103
NAMNUNG: "Oh, I'm really drunk tonight.
Come pick me up."

483
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:07,938
KONG: But what if they don't come?

484
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,481
NAMNUNG: That's their problem.

485
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:10,649
NAMNUNG: I can just go home by myself.

486
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:11,900
KONG: That's the end of it.

487
00:19:12,442 --> 00:19:13,235
KONG: That's the end of it.

488
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:14,570
NAMNUNG: That's his choice. Up to him.

489
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:15,696
KONG: Okay.

490
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:17,906
NAMNUNG: My turn.

491
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:19,366
NAMNUNG: This one's fun. I like it.

492
00:19:20,242 --> 00:19:21,856
- NAMNUNG: Call every night.
- KONG: Call every night.

493
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:23,871
NAMNUNG: "Call every night" isn't a message, right?

494
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,081
NAMNUNG: But what if "call every night" is an action?

495
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:27,124
KONG: If it's an action...

496
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:28,125
NAMNUNG: Would we do that with just friends?

497
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:31,753
- NAMNUNG: Sure. Doing it with friends is fine.
- KONG: Yeah, you can do it with friends.

498
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:38,051
- KONG: Right, I'm updating my life with
my friends every day. - NAMNUNG: Gossiping.

499
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:40,262
NAMNUNG: And I talk longer than I do
with the person I'm talking to.

500
00:19:40,352 --> 00:19:45,017
- KONG: Sometimes I only talk to them for 30 minutes.
- NAMNUNG: But I talk to my friends for 2 hours.

501
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:46,727
KONG: You get carried away.

502
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:47,769
KONG: I'm home now.

503
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:50,606
KONG: But I send this text every day,
always letting them know.

504
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,024
KONG: Who would you send this text to?

505
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:53,609
NAMNUNG: I'd send it to friends.

506
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:54,776
KONG: But every day, right?

507
00:19:55,402 --> 00:19:56,195
NAMNUNG: Every day?

508
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:56,987
KONG: Yes, every day.

509
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:58,488
NAMNUNG: If every day, it must be my dad.

510
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:02,743
NAMNUNG: I'm home now. I'm going to school now.

511
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:04,119
KONG: If I look at it from another angle,

512
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:10,464
KONG: I feel like it could be a way
to reassure the person I'm talking to.

513
00:20:10,709 --> 00:20:11,877
KONG: Like, "I'm home now",

514
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:13,003
KONG: things like that,

515
00:20:13,003 --> 00:20:13,587
KONG: "What are you up to?"

516
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,087
KONG: Stuff like that.

517
00:20:14,087 --> 00:20:16,381
- KONG: So I feel like...
- NAMNUNG: If it were me, I'd probably send it

518
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:17,591
NAMNUNG: to the person I'm talking to or my partner.

519
00:20:17,758 --> 00:20:19,426
NAMNUNG: I'm an extrovert who's also an introvert.

520
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:21,762
NAMNUNG: I don't like reporting every little thing.

521
00:20:21,856 --> 00:20:22,888
- NAMNUNG: Stuff like that.
- KONG: That much, huh?

522
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,139
NAMNUNG: So I kind of feel like...

523
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:30,854
NAMNUNG: Say I'm talking to someone who keeps texting,
"I'm eating now. I'm doing this."

524
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:36,068
NAMNUNG: "Good night. Good morning. I'm leaving home."
Stuff like that. I find it kind of boring.

525
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:37,069
KONG: Oh, really?

526
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:40,155
NAMNUNG: For me, it's like,
shouldn't we just go live our lives?

527
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:43,492
KONG: But for me, if it's a "I'm home now" message,

528
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:47,287
KONG: I'd only send it to someone
I really want to tell.

529
00:20:47,287 --> 00:20:50,207
KONG: "I'm home now" as a way of showing I'm sincere.

530
00:20:50,368 --> 00:20:53,377
NAMNUNG: But if you're dating,
they say they're going out,

531
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:55,754
NAMNUNG: and then they come home
without telling you and just fall asleep.

532
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:57,214
NAMNUNG: That would make me mad.

533
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:59,925
- KONG: If it were me, I wouldn't like that either.
- NAMNUNG: Like, "Don't you care at all?"

534
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,760
KONG: Say they tell you they're going out for BBQ pork.

535
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,264
KONG: They might not really be
at the BBQ place, you know?

536
00:21:03,424 --> 00:21:04,640
- NAMNUNG: Maybe they're out drinking, you know?
- KONG: Could be.

537
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:08,433
KONG: So I feel like telling the truth like that
is the honest thing to do.

538
00:21:08,475 --> 00:21:11,812
KONG: Not like being at a bar and then
what are you supposed to do with that?

539
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:16,525
NAMNUNG: It's probably something we'd only do
for someone we really like.

540
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:17,401
KONG: Yeah. This kind of message.

541
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:19,987
NAMNUNG: That's when we'd act in a way

542
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:21,196
NAMNUNG: that's not normally like us.

543
00:21:21,321 --> 00:21:22,155
KONG: Mm, I get it.

544
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:23,198
KONG: One more question.

545
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,867
NAMNUNG: Make the last one a good one.

546
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:29,621
NAMNUNG: They might be busy.
If this person messages every 2 AM

547
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:33,792
NAMNUNG: and never texts in the morning,
like you text them first...

548
00:21:34,918 --> 00:21:36,253
NAMNUNG: You might already be asleep at 2 AM.

549
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:39,881
NAMNUNG: Then you text back at 10 AM,
and they don't reply.

550
00:21:39,881 --> 00:21:43,760
NAMNUNG: They text again at 2 AM.
Like always. What do they want?

551
00:21:44,052 --> 00:21:47,392
KONG: Honestly, it's kind of tricky
if we're in that situation.

552
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:51,935
KONG: You try to chat or answer them
in the morning, and they don't reply at all.

553
00:21:51,935 --> 00:21:55,022
KONG: They only ever reply
at one or two in the morning.

554
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:57,088
KONG: What are you even doing?

555
00:21:57,344 --> 00:21:59,943
KONG: I think I wouldn't do this to friends,
because I feel like

556
00:21:59,968 --> 00:22:02,321
KONG: if it's friends,
we're already talking all the time.

557
00:22:02,321 --> 00:22:05,782
KONG: We'd just reply anyway, like at lunch,
when we wake up, whenever.

558
00:22:05,782 --> 00:22:07,701
NAMNUNG: They might work night shifts, who knows.

559
00:22:07,868 --> 00:22:11,288
KONG: But replying like "doing something,
going out" at night doesn't feel right.

560
00:22:11,621 --> 00:22:12,414
NAMNUNG: Ever had that?

561
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:13,290
KONG: Yeah, I have.

562
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:13,957
NAMNUNG: Me too.

563
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:16,752
KONG: Same here. In the morning, a DM or a reply.

564
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:19,921
KONG: They reply to stories, but never in the morning.

565
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:22,674
KONG: Then they reply again at night
because they feel like it. You get the vibe?

566
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:26,386
KONG: They reply like this,
"Still awake? Why are you up so late?"

567
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:29,216
KONG: Why not talk in the morning instead of now?

568
00:22:29,973 --> 00:22:30,891
KONG: I'm going to sleep.

569
00:22:31,099 --> 00:22:34,353
NAMNUNG: I've had that too.
They reply in the morning, but kind of like...

570
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:36,563
NAMNUNG: They reply after a few hours, but at night...

571
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:37,689
NAMNUNG: Oh, wow, they reply super fast.

572
00:22:37,731 --> 00:22:39,524
- NAMNUNG: What are you hoping for?
- KONG: And suddenly, you're replying so fast.

573
00:22:40,108 --> 00:22:41,526
KONG: Suddenly you've got all this free time.

574
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:43,648
- KONG: You really can't tell, huh?
- NAMNUNG: Pretty much.

575
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:45,489
NAMNUNG: That last game was really fun.

576
00:22:45,572 --> 00:22:46,365
NAMNUNG: But I've got a question.

577
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:49,848
NAMNUNG: Are you the type to let the other talk first,

578
00:22:49,848 --> 00:22:50,827
NAMNUNG: or do you speak first?

579
00:22:50,827 --> 00:22:54,176
NAMNUNG: Like when there's a problem,
or when you're flirting with someone.

580
00:22:54,331 --> 00:22:58,502
KONG: If I feel like there's a problem,
or I get this sense that

581
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:01,797
KONG: something's off and not right,
then I'll be the one to speak first.

582
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:07,636
KONG: I feel like if I don't say anything
and they don't say anything, nothing will start.

583
00:23:08,178 --> 00:23:11,932
KONG: And I'm naturally talkative,
so if there's a problem, I can tell.

584
00:23:11,932 --> 00:23:16,311
KONG: Like if you're sulking but acting
like nothing's wrong and all that,

585
00:23:16,311 --> 00:23:18,688
KONG: I'll ask right away what's wrong.

586
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:23,296
NAMNUNG: What about flirting?
Do you make the first move or wait for them?

587
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:27,406
KONG: For me, I'd rather have people come to me.

588
00:23:27,406 --> 00:23:32,452
KONG: Because I'm shy about flirting.
I don't know what'll happen if I go up to them.

589
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,538
KONG: I wouldn't know how to act.

590
00:23:34,704 --> 00:23:37,958
KONG: So I'd rather have people flirt with me.

591
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:42,254
KONG: Because at least I know how to respond.
They're here to flirt with me.

592
00:23:42,879 --> 00:23:45,715
NAMNUNG: Yeah, same. Like, whether you're
the one waiting to be pursued

593
00:23:45,715 --> 00:23:50,720
NAMNUNG: or the one who goes for it,
I feel like it depends on the other person's vibe.

594
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,472
NAMNUNG: If they seem like someone

595
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:56,852
NAMNUNG: who has that cute, playful vibe,
I'll flirt with them first.

596
00:23:56,852 --> 00:24:01,523
NAMNUNG: Because when someone's into us,
we can feel it.

597
00:24:01,523 --> 00:24:05,444
NAMNUNG: But most of the time, I don't make
the first move. I wait for others to flirt with me.

598
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:09,364
NAMNUNG: Because I feel like when I really
want a partner, I might grab the wrong person.

599
00:24:09,698 --> 00:24:15,454
NAMNUNG: Something like that happened before,
so I changed my mindset about wanting a partner.

600
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:18,290
NAMNUNG: I'll wait for someone to come to me
if they really like me.

601
00:24:18,415 --> 00:24:20,928
KONG: I've been there too. Sometimes I really
wanted a partner

602
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:25,422
KONG: and lowered my standards to approach
another person, get the feel?

603
00:24:25,696 --> 00:24:29,593
KONG: Sometimes I just really want a partner
after being single for so long.

604
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:33,889
KONG: You're willing to lower your standards
for them, but once you really talk,

605
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:38,685
KONG: they're not what you wanted. You don't need
to lower your standards just to have a partner.

606
00:24:39,811 --> 00:24:45,150
NAMNUNG: So, how long was your
longest situationship or talking stage?

607
00:24:45,525 --> 00:24:46,359
NAMNUNG: And how did it end?

608
00:24:46,526 --> 00:24:49,488
KONG: Believe it or not, it went on for almost
a year and we were still nothing.

609
00:24:49,856 --> 00:24:52,699
KONG: So I felt like, if we're going to keep
talking for seven or eight months,

610
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:55,744
KONG: I'd rather be in a relationship
and really get to know each other.

611
00:24:55,744 --> 00:25:00,123
KONG: That way it still feels okay. We're officially
together and getting to know each other.

612
00:25:00,544 --> 00:25:05,003
KONG: But sometimes we talk to them so long
it feels like we already know everything.

613
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,172
KONG: So we feel like, "Okay,
we don't need to be a couple."

614
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:11,092
KONG: So we were fine ending it,
saying we'd learned enough.

615
00:25:11,092 --> 00:25:15,055
KONG: Over those seven or eight months,
I realized what I wanted

616
00:25:15,055 --> 00:25:16,681
KONG: just wasn't in you at all.

617
00:25:17,307 --> 00:25:20,101
NAMNUNG: I picked this question
because I opened up about it earlier.

618
00:25:20,101 --> 00:25:23,808
NAMNUNG: I hate wasting time,
so if you're not interested...

619
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:26,525
NAMNUNG: No need to keep talking.
If you're really interested, just date me.

620
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:29,069
NAMNUNG: It all ends the same.

621
00:25:29,248 --> 00:25:31,988
KONG: Yeah, you can be a couple first
and get to know each other later.

622
00:25:32,072 --> 00:25:33,406
NAMNUNG: Yeah, but the pros and cons are different.

623
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:34,282
KONG: Oh, yeah.

624
00:25:34,282 --> 00:25:38,495
NAMNUNG: It's like, why not just give each other
a status, like, okay, we're a couple.

625
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:40,807
KONG: And no one decides how long it has to be

626
00:25:40,807 --> 00:25:42,874
- KONG: before you're a couple, right?
- NAMNUNG: Right.

627
00:25:43,166 --> 00:25:45,377
KONG: Actually, we might even feel
a spark from the very start.

628
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:46,920
KONG: We might want to be a couple
from the first month.

629
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:48,088
KONG: It can happen.

630
00:25:48,171 --> 00:25:48,547
NAMNUNG: Yes.

631
00:25:48,547 --> 00:25:53,134
KONG: It doesn't have to be five months or more.
You don't need ages of talking before you're a couple.

632
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:58,598
NAMNUNG: It's like I'm already sure about you,
and I'm saying that we've been talking.

633
00:25:58,598 --> 00:26:00,892
NAMNUNG: I want to keep talking
and actually be your partner.

634
00:26:01,184 --> 00:26:04,104
NAMNUNG: By now you should know, if you feel the same,

635
00:26:04,104 --> 00:26:06,314
NAMNUNG: you should be asking me to be your partner.

636
00:26:06,314 --> 00:26:10,527
- NAMNUNG: You'd probably agree,
but you might be thinking... - KONG: Exactly.

637
00:26:10,527 --> 00:26:14,489
NAMNUNG: Like, having me
still isn't enough for you, is it?

638
00:26:14,489 --> 00:26:17,242
NAMNUNG: You still don't want to be my partner.
You don't really want to know me.

639
00:26:17,242 --> 00:26:23,290
NAMNUNG: Maybe you're just waiting for someone
better than me to come into your life.

640
00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:26,543
NAMNUNG: So it's like we were never
equally into each other.

641
00:26:26,543 --> 00:26:27,085
KONG: Yeah.

642
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:29,921
NAMNUNG: So it just feels like, "Okay,
this is a waste of time if we're just going to

643
00:26:30,505 --> 00:26:32,257
NAMNUNG: stay talking like this."

644
00:26:32,299 --> 00:26:35,176
NAMNUNG: Because I once started talking
to someone in Grade 7.

645
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:39,456
NAMNUNG: All the way until Grade 10. We talked
for four years, and never became a couple.

646
00:26:39,889 --> 00:26:40,890
KONG: Yeah, it happens.

647
00:26:41,099 --> 00:26:42,601
NAMNUNG: You get it now, right?
That's how it ended up like this.

648
00:26:43,351 --> 00:26:46,813
NAMNUNG: Feels like such a waste of my life, you know?
So now, whenever I talk to someone, I give it my all.

649
00:26:46,813 --> 00:26:50,108
NAMNUNG: Three-month limit. If you still
don't want to be my partner by then, you're free to go.

650
00:26:50,817 --> 00:26:52,611
NAMNUNG: So that means, in this relationship,

651
00:26:52,694 --> 00:26:53,903
NAMNUNG: I can't expect anything from you anymore.

652
00:26:54,195 --> 00:26:55,530
NAMNUNG: We've talked quite a bit now.

653
00:26:56,406 --> 00:26:58,575
NAMNUNG: And we've learned quite a lot too.

654
00:26:58,825 --> 00:26:59,534
NAMNUNG: Have you ever watched our show?

655
00:26:59,534 --> 00:26:59,951
KONG: Yeah, I have.

656
00:26:59,951 --> 00:27:00,910
- NAMNUNG: The first episode.
- KONG: Just the first episode.

657
00:27:01,161 --> 00:27:04,122
NAMNUNG: It's time for us to do reaction.

658
00:27:04,331 --> 00:27:05,874
KONG: Ah, okay.

659
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:09,461
NAMNUNG: We picked this one because we saw

660
00:27:10,003 --> 00:27:13,006
